# Problem 13 – Longest Word

### Code

```python
a = "I LOVE LEARNING PYTHON"

words = a.split()

longest = words[0]

for word in words:
    if len(word) > len(longest):
        longest = word

print(longest)
```

### Output

```text
LEARNING
```

### Logic

- Compare lengths of all words.
- Store the longest word.

